title: Act4_Decisions_Confront
---
<<set_route YarnManager Decisions_Confront>>

<<set_portrait YarnManager Cyrus>>
Cyrus: I’m going to say something, and I need you to stay calm. Okay?

<<set_portrait YarnManager Eve>>
Eve: Uh, okay?

<<set_portrait YarnManager Cyrus>>
Cyrus: I need to understand something.
Cyrus: ...
Cyrus: I know you’re a False Human.

<<set_portrait YarnManager Eve>>
Eve: ...What?

<<set_portrait YarnManager Cyrus>>
Cyrus: Listen to me. I’m not gonna hurt you, or do anything. I just want to talk.

<<set_portrait YarnManager Eve>>
Eve: Why would you- how could you-

<<set_portrait YarnManager Cyrus>>
Cyrus: I know about Ava.

<<set_portrait YarnManager Eve>>
Eve: No, I- I didn’t- I didn’t mean to- How do you even know her name? WHO are you?

<<set_portrait YarnManager Cyrus>>
Cyrus: Let’s just say...I can see things beyond our timeline. A power of Fate.

<<set_portrait YarnManager Eve>>
Eve: I don’t- I don’t know how you know all this but- you weren’t there.

<<set_portrait YarnManager Cyrus>>
Cyrus: Then tell me. Tell me your side. I want to hear it from you. Your story.

<<set_portrait YarnManager Eve>>
Eve: Cyrus...

<<set_portrait YarnManager Cyrus>>
Cyrus: I know what the Hierophant intends to do with you. You’re not just a tool. You’re not just... a step in someone else’s ritual.

<<set_portrait YarnManager Eve>>
Eve: Stop. Please stop saying it like that.

<<set_portrait YarnManager Cyrus>>
Cyrus: I’m trying to help you.

<<set_portrait YarnManager Eve>>
Eve: You can’t.
Eve: You will not stop the Assimilation from happening.
Eve: Under the Hierophant we will all be one.

<<set_portrait YarnManager Cyrus>>
Cyrus: Ah. I see.
===


title: Act4_Decisions_RunAway
---
<<set_route YarnManager Decisions_RunAway>>

<<set_portrait YarnManager Eve>>
Eve: And as I was saying, the monsters are appearing closer to the residential districts now.
Eve: Even the shelters aren’t safe anymore. People are pretending everything is normal, but... everyone’s scared.

<<set_portrait YarnManager Cyrus>>
Cyrus: Forgive me if this is a stupid question, but why hasn't everyone just left? We could just run away together.

<<set_portrait YarnManager Eve>>
Eve: There isn’t anywhere safer.

<<set_portrait YarnManager Cyrus>>
Cyrus: There has to be somewhere beyond the outskirts.

<<set_portrait YarnManager Eve>>
Eve: The outskirts are a disaster zone, Cyrus.
Eve: Most roads are gone. Half the districts are overrun by monsters or memory storms. Even caravans with armed escorts disappear out there.
Eve: Normal people can’t do anything. Maybe hunters with strong enough Fates could survive the journey, but not everyone.
Eve: My family is here. The people at the shelter are here. Everyone I care about is still here.
Eve: How could I run away while leaving them behind to die?
Eve: Besides... I don’t think I could leave even if I wanted to.

<<set_portrait YarnManager Cyrus>>
Cyrus: What do you mean?

<<set_portrait YarnManager Eve>>
Eve: I don’t know how to explain it properly. It’s just... 
Eve: Sometimes I wonder if people are just shaped by the places they’re born in.
Eve: Like no matter how much they struggle, there are some things they can never truly escape.

<<set_portrait YarnManager Cyrus>>
Cyrus: [i]Does she mean...[/i]
Cyrus: [i]False humans are born from memories. And memories cannot stray far from their origin.[/i]
Cyrus: [i]Eve may never have had the freedom to choose escape at all.[/i]

<<set_portrait YarnManager Eve>>
Eve: Anyway, you should stop suggesting dramatic things like “running away together.” It sounds like something from one of those romance novels.

<<set_portrait YarnManager Cyrus>>
Cyrus: Heh.
===


title: Act4_Decisions_SpendTime
---
<<set_route YarnManager Decisions_SpendTime>>
<<set_flag YarnManager Act4_Decisions_SpendTime>>

<<set_portrait YarnManager Cyrus>>
Cyrus: [i]I need to learn more about Eve.[/i]
Cyrus: [i]Everything she’s done for me couldn’t have been a farce, right?[/i]
Cyrus: [i]There has to be something else I can do...[/i]
<<clear_portrait YarnManager>>
: [i]The two go to the shop.[/i]
<<set_portrait YarnManager Eve>>
Eve: Hey Dad, do you need help with anything?
<<set_portrait YarnManager Shopkeeper>>
Shopkeeper: I’m all good for now. And actually...
Shopkeeper: One of the Hunters you helped last week dropped by earlier and left a movie as thanks.
<<set_portrait YarnManager Eve>>
Eve: Oh, really? Thanks, Dad! And tell him I said thank you!
<<set_portrait YarnManager Cyrus>>
Cyrus: You like watching movies?
<<set_portrait YarnManager Eve>>
Eve: Psh, I’m not a full-on cinephile or anything. It’s just something I like to do when I don’t have much else going on.
Eve: Actually, want to come to my room and see my collection?
Eve: Welcome to my room! It’s a little messy, aha...
Eve: Anyhow, let’s see what this is.
Eve: Oooh, it’s a new Heartline Pictures movie!
Eve: It’s called “Fatefully Yours in Lumas.”
<<clear_portrait YarnManager>>
: [i]The description says: “Margaret, an ambitious city memory-writer, returns to her hometown of Lumas to help her family’s struggling shop.[/i]
: [i]But when she meets Krys, a charming Hunter with a tragic past, she must choose between the life she built in the city and the love waiting for her at home.”[/i]
<<set_portrait YarnManager Cyrus>>
Cyrus: ...Sounds pretty cheesy.
<<set_portrait YarnManager Eve>>
Eve: Hey, don’t judge my taste in movies! Romcoms are perfectly good movies in their own right!
Eve: The lighthearted comedy paired with the heart-melting romantic elements make them both funny and sweet to watch,
Eve: and the less complex story with lower stakes makes it so you can easily watch them together with your friends and family and have fun! And ALSO-
<<set_portrait YarnManager Cyrus>>
Cyrus: For someone who claims to not be a movie-lover, you sure have a lot to say about them.
<<set_portrait YarnManager Eve>>
Eve: Ehehehe...
Eve: Anyhow, want to watch a movie with me? There's no mission right now.
<<set_portrait YarnManager Cyrus>>
Cyrus: [i]Guess I defeated the monsters too fast this time.[/i]
Cyrus: Sure. What do you have?
<<set_portrait YarnManager Eve>>
Eve: We have a slice of life. The other is a murder mystery.
Eve: And of course, we can watch the new one together if you’re in the mood for some romcom!
Eve: So? Which one do you want to watch?
-> [i]Slice of Life[/i]
    <<jump Act4_Decisions_SpendTime_SliceofLife>>
-> [i]Murder Mystery[/i]
    <<jump Act4_Decisions_SpendTime_Drama>>
-> [i]Romcom[/i]
    <<jump Act4_Decisions_SpendTime_Romcom>>
===


