title: Act4_LunaSearch_Confront
---
<<set_route YarnManager LunaSearch_Confront>>

<<set_portrait YarnManager Luna>>
Luna: Oh, good-!
Luna: You!

<<set_portrait YarnManager PoliceNPC>>
Officer: Captain-

<<set_portrait YarnManager Luna>>
Luna: Go make yourself useful, I’m busy.
Luna: I can't believe you'd dare steal that face. You monster.

<<set_portrait YarnManager Cyrus>>
Cyrus: Wait, wait, I don't want to fight!

<<set_portrait YarnManager Luna>>
Luna: Then don’t.

<<set_portrait YarnManager Cyrus>>
Cyrus: Not when you're holding out your blade like that! 

<<set_portrait YarnManager Luna>>
Luna: We’ll go elsewhere. I’m not having this conversation in front of civilians.

<<set_portrait YarnManager Cyrus>>
Cyrus: [i]I told Eve I’d be going. Hm? This is the outskirts again-[/i]
Cyrus: ! I thought we were going to talk it out!

<<set_portrait YarnManager Luna>>
Luna: Never said that.

TODO split these into 2 separate scenes lol

<<set_portrait YarnManager Cyrus>>
Cyrus: *huff huff* [i]How is she so powerful? She's not even an enforcer.[/i]

<<set_portrait YarnManager Luna>>
Luna: Any last words? 

<<clear_portrait YarnManager>>
[i]A meminiscor emerges from the bushes and lunges at Cyrus, before Luna shoots it dead.[/i]

<<set_portrait YarnManager Cyrus>>
Cyrus: See??? How could that thing come at me if I’m a false human?

<<set_portrait YarnManager Luna>>
Luna: ...
Luna: So you aren’t a false human, then. Lovely. But there’s lots of skinwalkers out there. Slaves of the Arcanas.

<<set_portrait YarnManager Luna>>
Luna: Which one are you?

<<set_portrait YarnManager Cyrus>>
Cyrus: Please, I really am on your side! I’m trying to stop the Assimilation.

<<set_portrait YarnManager Luna>>
Luna: Then why haven't you killed the remaining false human? You clearly know about them.

<<set_portrait YarnManager Cyrus>>
Cyrus: ...This is out of their control.
Cyrus: Condemning an innocent person for something beyond their control? I can’t do that.
Cyrus: What if we could find another way? Don’t we owe it to them to at least try?

<<set_portrait YarnManager Luna>>
Luna: So what if they’re innocent now? There will inevitably come a day when they aren’t.
Luna: If you truly are a follower of justice, then you know that a threat to the greater good must be eliminated.

<<set_portrait YarnManager Cyrus>>
Cyrus: It’s not that simple.

<<set_portrait YarnManager Luna>>
Luna: It is. You can’t let your pity get in the way of what needs to be done.

